2026-05-13 15:51:16 [DEBUG] llm.engine: ARGS: ('\n    You are a workflow concierge agent. Interpret the user\'s request into a structured intent.\n\n    User message:\n    run it\n\n    There is no pending intent.\n\n\n    Current workflow description:\n    Here\'s an overview of the workflow:\n\n Load Ideas (\'start\')\n- What it does: Load all ideas from storage before browsing.\n\n Select Idea (\'select_idea\')\n- What it does: User browses, searches, and selects an idea.\n- Produces: select_idea\n\n Create Asset Definition Options (\'create_asset_definition_options\')\n- What it does: System generates asset options from idea.\n- Produces: asset_definitions\n\n Select the Asset Definition to Generate (\'select_asset_def\')\n- What it does: User browses and selects asset to generate.\n- Produces: select_asset_def\n\n Edit dialogue segment (\'dialogue_selection\')\n- What it does: Refine the selected portion of the dialogue.\n- Depends on: select_asset_def\n- Produces: dialogue_selection\n- Agent hints: The user can ask to trim, shorten, expand, or otherwise refine the selected dialogue segment. Interpret natural language edits and apply them to the DialogueSegmentSelection object.\n\n Finalize Asset Definition (\'finalize_asset\')\n- What it does: Edit the singleton asset params.\n- Depends on: dialogue_selection\n- Produces: final_asset_definition\n\n\n    Valid values for "intent" (with descriptions):\n    - "list_workflow_items" — User wants to list recent items or runs in the workflow.\n- "describe_workflow" — User wants a human-readable explanation of the workflow\n- "load_recent" — User wants to load the most recent item\n- "create_item" — create a new workflow item.\n- "confirm_pending" — User is confirming the previously proposed action or item in a pending clarification.\n- "reject_pending" — User is rejecting the previously proposed action or item and wants to choose another.\n- "cancel_pending" — User wants to cancel the pending action and return to normal conversation.\n- "idle" — Unclear or no actionable intent; agent should ask for clarification.\n- "search_ideas" — Search or browse ideas/cases by keyword or phrase.\n- "review_idea_metadata" — Make edits to the current case/idea information.\n- "reset_idea_metadata" — Reset the idea information.\n- "approve_idea" — Approve the currently selected idea and continue the workflow.\n- "review_final_asset_definition" — Make edits to the asset definition info.\n- "reset_final_asset_definition" — Reset the asset information.\n- "approve_final_asset_definition" — Approve the fully edited asset definition and continue to export.\n- "get_more_ideas" — Trigger the idea generation workflow to expand the idea universe.\n- "select_idea_by_reference" — Select a specific idea from the search results or full idea list.\n- "approve_idea_metadata" — Approve case or idea information.\n- "describe_asset_defs" — Describe the current asset definitions.\n- "select_asset_def_by_reference" — Select or choose a specific option from asset definitions.\n- "approve_asset_def" — Approve asset definition.\n- "approve_dialogue_selection" — Approve the dialogue selection.\n- "reset_dialogue_selection" — Reset or Revert the dialogue selection.\n- "edit_dialogue_selection" — Edit or refine the selected dialogue segment using natural‑language instructions.\n- "approve_asset_definition" — Approve the selected asset definition and continue the workflow.\n- "edit_asset_definition_field" — Edit a specific field of the current asset definition.\n- "select_asset_definition" — Workflow step: user browses and selects an asset definition option.\n- "edit_asset_definition" — Workflow step: user edits the chosen asset definition.\n\n    Examples for disambiguation:\n    Intent "describe_workflow" examples:\n- describe the current workflow\n\nIntent "load_recent" examples:\n- load the recent item\n\nIntent "create_item" examples:\n- let\'s create a new item\n- let\'s start it\n- run it\n\nIntent "review_idea_metadata" examples:\n- let\'s change the name\n- please edit the description\n- remove Mr. Katyal as a speaker\n\nIntent "reset_idea_metadata" examples:\n- let\'s reset the info\n- let\'s go back to the original case info\n\nIntent "approve_idea" examples:\n- use this idea\n- approve this one\n- select this idea\n\nIntent "review_final_asset_definition" examples:\n- let\'s change the name\n- let\'s edit the description\n- remove Mr. Katyal as a speaker\n\nIntent "reset_final_asset_definition" examples:\n- let\'s reset the asset metadata\n- let\'s go back to the original asset info\n\nIntent "approve_final_asset_definition" examples:\n- approve this final version\n- looks good, move on\n\nIntent "get_more_ideas" examples:\n- get more ideas\n- generate new ideas\n- refresh ideas\n\nIntent "select_idea_by_reference" examples:\n- {\'user\': \'select idea 3\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'select_idea_by_reference\', \'parameters\': {\'reference\': \'3\'}}}\n- {\'user\': \'use the immigration case\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'select_idea_by_reference\', \'parameters\': {\'reference\': \'immigration\'}}}\n- {\'user\': \'pick Brown v. Board\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'select_idea_by_reference\', \'parameters\': {\'reference\': \'brown\'}}}\n\nIntent "approve_idea_metadata" examples:\n- approve this case info\n- let\'s approve this idea\n\nIntent "describe_asset_defs" examples:\n- what are the asset definitions\n- what are the options?\n\nIntent "select_asset_def_by_reference" examples:\n- {\'user\': \'select idea 3\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'select_idea_by_reference\', \'parameters\': {\'reference\': \'3\'}}}\n- {\'user\': \'use the immigration case\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'select_idea_by_reference\', \'parameters\': {\'reference\': \'immigration\'}}}\n- {\'user\': \'pick Brown v. Board\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'select_idea_by_reference\', \'parameters\': {\'reference\': \'brown\'}}}\n\nIntent "approve_asset_def" examples:\n- approve this asset definition info\n- let\'s approve this option\n\nIntent "approve_dialogue_selection" examples:\n- let\'s approve this\n- okay let\'s go to the next step\n\nIntent "reset_dialogue_selection" examples:\n- revert the dialogue to the original\n- let\'s go back to the original dialogue\n\nIntent "edit_dialogue_selection" examples:\n- {\'user\': \'cut the first speaker\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'edit_dialogue_selection\', \'parameters\': {\'edit_instruction\': \'cut the first speaker\'}}}\n- {\'user\': "start the excerpt at Gorsuch\'s second question", \'intent\': {\'name\': \'edit_dialogue_selection\', \'parameters\': {\'edit_instruction\': "start the excerpt at Gorsuch\'s second question"}}}\n- {\'user\': \'make this shorter\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'edit_dialogue_selection\', \'parameters\': {\'edit_instruction\': \'make this shorter\'}}}\n- {\'user\': \'trim everything before the lawyer starts talking\', \'intent\': {\'name\': \'edit_dialogue_selection\', \'parameters\': {\'edit_instruction\': \'trim everything before the lawyer starts talking\'}}}\n\nIntent "approve_asset_definition" examples:\n- approve this asset definition\n- this one looks good\n\nIntent "edit_asset_definition_field" examples:\n- set title_final to \'The Future of Free Speech\'\n- change hook_final to \'A landmark case with national implications\'\n- set clip_start to 12.5\n\nIntent "select_asset_definition" examples:\n- start selecting an asset definition\n\nIntent "edit_asset_definition" examples:\n- start editing the asset definition\n\n    Return ONLY a JSON object matching this schema:\n\n    {\n      "intent": string,\n      "reasoning": string | null\n    }\n\n    Respond ONLY with valid JSON. Do not include commentary.\n',)
